    "year": 1665,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "44.5 cm × 39 cm",
    "location": "Mauritshuis, The Hague",
    "description": "Often called the 'Mona Lisa of the North,' Vermeer's intimate portrait captures a young woman in a moment of turning, her luminous pearl earring catching the light. The painting's power lies in its simplicity — a dark background, a striking blue and gold turban, and the girl's captivating, ambiguous gaze.",
