    "year": 1818,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "94.8 cm × 74.8 cm",
    "location": "Hamburger Kunsthalle, Hamburg",
    "description": "The quintessential Romantic painting shows a solitary figure standing atop a rocky precipice, gazing out over a vast landscape shrouded in mist. Friedrich captures the Romantic ideal of the sublime — the overwhelming power and beauty of nature that dwarfs human existence yet elevates the individual spirit.",
