    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "260 cm × 325 cm",
    "location": "Musée du Louvre, Paris",
    "description": "Delacroix's iconic painting commemorates the July Revolution of 1830 with a powerful allegory of Liberty personified as a bare-breasted woman leading the people over the barricades. The painting's dramatic composition, smoky atmosphere, and bold use of the French tricolor make it one of the most recognizable political artworks ever created.",
    "image": "/paintings/liberty-leading-the-people.jpg",
