    "location": "Metropolitan Museum of Art, New York",
    "description": "Hokusai's iconic woodblock print depicts a towering wave threatening boats near the coast of Kanagawa, with Mount Fuji visible in the background. The dramatic composition, bold lines, and striking use of Prussian blue made this print a sensation that profoundly influenced Western Impressionist and Art Nouveau movements.",
