    "year": 1821,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "130.2 cm × 185.4 cm",
    "location": "National Gallery, London",
    "description": "Constable's beloved painting depicts a rural scene near Flatford Mill in Suffolk, with a hay cart crossing a shallow river beneath a sky of luminous, ever-changing clouds. The painting's naturalistic treatment of light and atmosphere, painted partly outdoors, anticipated the Impressionist movement by half a century.",
