    "year": 1872,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "48 cm × 63 cm",
    "location": "Musée Marmottan Monet, Paris",
    "description": "The painting that gave Impressionism its name captures the port of Le Havre at dawn. Monet's loose, rapid brushstrokes dissolve solid forms into shimmering reflections of light on water. The orange sun, barely brighter than the surrounding grey-blue atmosphere, creates a haunting study in atmospheric color.",
    "image": "/paintings/impression-sunrise.jpg",
    "imageCredit": "Wikimedia Commons, Public Domain",
    "movementId": "impressionism",
